@startuml PostApiIssueParallel

title Idempotent POST Issue - Parallel Request Case (Same UUID from different browser tabs)

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #F9A825

autonumber

actor "Browser Tab 1" as tab1
actor "Browser Tab 2" as tab2
participant "API Service" as api
database "Idempotency\nStore" as idStore
database "Orders DB" as db

== Same User sends same request with same UUID from 2 browser tabs ==
par Tab 1: POST with UUID=abc123
  tab1 -> api : POST /orders\nIdempotency-Key: abc123\n(body: item=A, qty=1)
  api -> idStore : CHECK idempotency key abc123
  idStore <-- api : NOT FOUND (key not yet stored)
else Tab 2: POST with UUID=abc123
  tab2 -> api : POST /orders\nIdempotency-Key: abc123\n(body: item=A, qty=1)
  api -> idStore : CHECK idempotency key abc123
  idStore <-- api : NOT FOUND (key not yet stored)
end

note right of api
RACE CONDITION:
Both requests see key as NOT FOUND
because neither has completed the
store operation yet. Read-then-insert
is NOT atomic.
end note

== Both requests proceed to insert ==
par Tab 1 Insert
  api -> db : INSERT order (item=A, qty=1)
  db <-- api : OK (order_id=301)
  api -> idStore : STORE key abc123 + response
else Tab 2 Insert
  api -> db : INSERT order (item=A, qty=1)
  db <-- api : OK (order_id=302)
  api -> idStore : STORE key abc123 + response
end

api --> tab1 : 201 Created (order_id=301)
api --> tab2 : 201 Created (order_id=302)

note bottom
PROBLEM:
Despite same Idempotency-Key (UUID),
two duplicate orders are created.
The duplicate prevention failed due to
non-atomic check-then-act window.

ROOT CAUSE:
Without atomic guarantee, concurrent
requests bypass idempotency protection.
end note

@enduml

